      <li styleclass="HowTo STEP">INTRODUCTION</li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Body Text">EC Software is committed to protecting your privacy. We do not sell, trade, or rent your personal information to others. Our website is structured so that you can visit and download trial software without identifying yourself or revealing any personal information.</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text"></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text">If you choose to provide us personally identifiable information (any information by which you can be identified), you can be assured that it will only be used to support your customer relationship with EC Software.</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text"></para>
    <list id="1" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="2" styleclass="HowTo STEP" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="HowTo STEP">HOW WE COLLECT YOUR PERSONAL INFORMATION</li>
      <list id="1" level="1" type="ol" listtype="lower-alpha" formatstring="&#37;&#49;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo STEP" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
        <li styleclass="HowTo STEP">Website Registration</li>
      </list>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Body Text">EC Software encourages users who want to participate in the EC Software support forums to register. In order to register, you must provide us with a username, password and a valid email address. This allows us to protect our community from abusive postings and provides a verifiable point of contact should legal questions arise. At any time, you have the ability to keep your email address hidden from other users by selecting that option within your user profile.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="line-height:1.00; tabstops:none;"></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text">When you register, you have the option of providing some additional information such as occupation, interests, and homepage URL. This optional information is made available to other forum users to foster a sense of community. If you have any concerns about providing this information, simply leave the fields blank and your registration will still be processed.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="line-height:1.00; tabstops:none;"></para>
