      <li styleclass="HowTo STEP">HOW WE USE YOUR PERSONAL INFORMATION</li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">EC Software generally uses your personal information to fulfill orders, process payments or perform credit check, as necessary, for interactive communications with you about our products, in order to prevent unlicensed or illegal use of EC Software software, to notify you by email or another medium about product upgrades, updated information, special offers and other new services or software offerings (you will be able to unsubscribe from emails by following the instructions at the bottom of our message).</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="line-height:1.00; tabstops:none;"></para>
    <list id="4" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="4" styleclass="HowTo STEP" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="HowTo STEP">HOW WE PROTECT AND STORE YOUR PERSONAL INFORMATION</li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="line-height:1.00; tabstops:none;"><text style="font-family:&apos;Times New Roman&apos;; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#000000;">EC Software has security measures in place to protect the loss, misuse and alteration of your personal information under our control. These include a firewall to prevent unauthorized access to our systems. Inside EC Software, personal information and customer data is stored in password-controlled servers with limited and controlled access on a need-to-know basis. While we cannot guarantee that loss, misuse or alteration to data will not occur, we take many precautions to prevent such unfortunate occurrences. However, EC Software accepts no liability for any unintentional disclosure. Your personal information is never shared outside EC Software.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="line-height:1.00; tabstops:none;"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="line-height:1.00; tabstops:none;"><text styleclass="text-strong" style="font-family:&apos;Times New Roman&apos;; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; font-style:normal; text-decoration:none; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#000000; background-color:transparent; letter-spacing:normal; letter-scaling:100%;">5. HOW WE USE COOKIES AND WEB LOGS</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="line-height:1.00; tabstops:none;"><text style="font-family:&apos;Times New Roman&apos;; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#000000;">The public areas of this website do not use cookies. When someone visits the website, a cookie may be placed on the user’s machine (if the user accepts cookies) or is read if the user has visited the website previously. By modifying your browser preferences you can choose to accept all cookies, to be notified when a cookie is set, or to reject all cookies. If you choose to not have your browser accept cookies from the website, you still will be able to view the website without restrictions. Web logs automatically record anything a web server sees, which may include email addresses you enter into a form or pages viewed by a user at a particular IP address.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="line-height:1.00; tabstops:none;"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="line-height:1.00; tabstops:none;"><text styleclass="text-strong" style="font-family:&apos;Times New Roman&apos;; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; font-style:normal; text-decoration:none; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#000000; background-color:transparent; letter-spacing:normal; letter-scaling:100%;">6. LINKS, DISCUSSION FORUM AND PUBLIC AREAS</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="line-height:1.00; tabstops:none;"><text style="font-family:&apos;Times New Roman&apos;; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#000000;">Our website contains links to other sites. EC Software takes no responsibility for the content or the privacy policies and practices of such Web sites. EC Software encourages you to read the privacy statements of these linked sites; their privacy practices may differ from ours. Please remember that any information you submit in a discussion forum, message board or other such area will be deemed public information and is not confidential. There is a risk in such communication venues that information can be collected and used by others.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="line-height:1.00; tabstops:none;"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="line-height:1.00; tabstops:none;"><text styleclass="text-strong" style="font-family:&apos;Times New Roman&apos;; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; font-style:normal; text-decoration:none; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#000000; background-color:transparent; letter-spacing:normal; letter-scaling:100%;">7. PROTECTION OF CHILDREN’S PERSONAL INFORMATION</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="line-height:1.00; tabstops:none;"><text style="font-family:&apos;Times New Roman&apos;; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#000000;">The website is not directed to children under the age of 13. If you are under 13 years of age you are not allowed to participate in the EC Software forums, purchase products or to provide any personal information on our website.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="line-height:1.00; tabstops:none;"></para>
